{"content":"---\ntitle: \"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"vbc42001\"\n  - \"bc42001\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"BC42001\"\nms.assetid: 31e7c383-894e-416c-b834-3688cc340ccf\n---\n# 'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported\n'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported. Use 'Sub New' to initialize a class.  \n  \n The `Class_Initialize` event of previous versions of Visual Basic is replaced by class constructors.  \n  \n By default, this message is a warning. For information on hiding warnings or treating warnings as errors, see [Configuring Warnings in Visual Basic](/visualstudio/ide/configuring-warnings-in-visual-basic).  \n  \n **Error ID:** BC42001  \n  \n## To correct this error  \n  \n-   Declare one or more `Sub` procedures named `New` to initialize a class. `Sub New` is called when a class instance is newly created.  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [Constructors](../programming-guide/concepts/object-oriented-programming.md#constructors)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,208],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"vbc42001\"\n  - \"bc42001\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"BC42001\"\nms.assetid: 31e7c383-894e-416c-b834-3688cc340ccf","nodes":[{"content":"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported","nodes":[{"pos":[0,47],"content":"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported","nodes":[{"content":"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported","pos":[0,47]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[215,262],"content":"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported","linkify":"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported","nodes":[{"content":"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported","pos":[0,47]}]},{"content":"'Class_Initialize' event is no longer supported.","pos":[263,311]},{"content":"Use 'Sub New' to initialize a class.","pos":[312,348]},{"pos":[355,455],"content":"T